org.agilewiki.jactor2.core.blades.transmutable

Interface Transmutable<DATATYPE>

  • Type Parameters:
    DATATYPE - The type of the unmodifiable form--typically an interface.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    TransmutableArrayList, TransmutableMap, TransmutableSet, TransmutableSortedMap, TransmutableSortedSet, TransmutableString, TSSMap

    public interface Transmutable<DATATYPE>
    An object which supports an unmodifiable (read-only) form. The unmodifiable form can be used with complete thread-safety for queries, while the creation of the unmodifiable form typically is not thread safe.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      Create a new unmodifyable form that reflects the latest changes until now.
